properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 17 at 4:16PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...Heavy Snow To Impact Travel Through the Evening...

.The slow moving system will produce snowfall rates of 1 to 2
inches per hour this afternoon and evening. A Winter Storm Warning
has been issued for Brown, Sibley, and Nicollet Counties, which
will see a couple more hours of heavy snow, and could have 7 to 10
inches by the time the snow ends this evening.

Precipitation will expand farther to the northeast across east
central Minnesota this evening. It will also linger into the
early evening as this system has slowed down a few hours.

A period of snow, occasionally heavy at times, will spread across
south central, and east central Minnesota, and into west central
Wisconsin through the early evening. The snow will end by 9 PM in
west central Wisconsin.

* WHAT...Heavy snow. Total snow accumulations of 7 to 10 inches.

* WHERE...Sibley, Brown and Nicollet Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
